The convertible eurobond issue announcedyesterday for Genentech Inc &lt;GENE.O> has been increased to atotal of 150 mln dlrs from 100 mln, Credit Suisse First BostonLtd (CSFB) said as lead manager.    The coupon has been set at five pct and conversion price at74 dlrs per share which represents a 23.85 pct premium overGenentech's stock closing level of 59.75 on the New York StockExchange last night.    Payment date has been brought forward to March 27 fromMarch 30 and the bonds will mature on March 27, 2002. REUTER&#3;